        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 10:45PM CDT by NWS Austin/San Antonio TX</headline>
        <description>At 1045 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Uvalde Estates, or 8 miles south of Uvalde, moving north at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Knippa, Uvalde Estates, Uvalde, Garner State Park, Reagan Wells,
Utopia, Concan, and Washer.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
